goal.core.program.rules

Class ForallDoRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • goal.parser.ParsedObject
      • goal.core.program.rules.Rule
        • goal.core.program.rules.ForallDoRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IParsedObject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ParsedObject>

    public class ForallDoRule
extends Rule

    A rule of the form:
        forall CONDITION do RESULT.

    Where CONDITION is a MentalStateCond, and RESULT an ActionCombo.

    When evaluated in a RuleSet, all possible substitutions that make the rule valid may be executed. If the rule is selected for execution, all valid substitutions must be executed.
    This type of rule can be located in any program{}-section of any module in a GOAL agent.

    Author:
    N.Kraayenbrink
